Set-up unit testing
  or create a new unit testing framework to use.
Some discovered options in research include:
  Google Test
    https://code.google.com/p/googletest/
  UnitTest++
    http://unittest-cpp.sourceforge.net/
  xUnit++
    https://bitbucket.org/moswald/xunit/wiki/Home
With some discussion and comparison articles here:
  http://gamesfromwithin.com/exploring-the-c-unit-testing-framework-jungle
  http://accu.org/index.php/journals/1326
  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_unit_testing_frameworks#C.2B.2B
  http://googletesting.blogspot.com/2012/10/why-are-there-so-many-c-testing.html
